The paper deals with natural language processing and machine learning techniques to classify the veracity of sentences using a trusted source of information. This falls under the scope of computational linguistics (cs.CL) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of semantic lexical frames from FrameNet also suggests a focus on language understanding and representation, which could fall under machine learning (cs.LG) and information retrieval (cs.IR). Finally, the evaluation of the model on the FEVER dataset suggests a focus on natural language inference and reasoning, which could also fall under neural networks (cs.NE).
